I am still dreaming of Hale and Hearty. I visited SF for work and ate here 4/5 days that I was in the area. The salads are freaking bomb dot com. I was obsessed with the spring salad. I added steak, medium rare and fell in love with every bite. The salad has everything you can imagine and it keeps you full all day. I think the salads are intended to be shared but I ate the whole thing every time because I didn't have a fridge in my room and because the salad was that good.

The ordering is weird. One line for salads and one for soups/sandwich's. Can fill out a salad sheet while you wait to make the process faster when you get up to where they make it. I had the half soup half sandwich combo. The sriracha chicken was really good and the bread was fantastic. The clam chowder wasn't as thick as I've had it other places but, was tasty as well. They have an "open faced" pot pie that looked really good. Will be stopping here more as the temperature drops.
